21. periuriorem periurus is simply “a liar” in Plautus, not “a perjurer,'' which is rather expressed by mendax. In this sense mendax is followed by gen. of object, si huius rei me esse mendacem inueneris As. v. 2. 5 ; credere has the same construc- tion As. ii. 4. 53, quoi omnium rerum ipsus semper credit.
